CIA - Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability

Attack Vectors - Entry point or route for attacker to gain access
eg- email, social media, removable devices, browsers, etc...
Security breach - get unauthorized access to device

Malware - a piece of software used by cybercriminals to infect systems and carry out actions that will cause harm
Two main components of Malware
(i) Propagation mechanism
(ii) Payload

(i) Propagation - how malware spreads itself across one or more systems
eg- virus, worm, trojan
(ii) Payload - the action that a piece of malware performs on an infected device or system
eg- ransomware, spyware, backdoors, botnet

